## Test Anti-Pattern Audit: `ProductCatalogTests.cs`

### Summary

**10 tests reviewed — 0 are effective.** This is a textbook **coverage-touching** suite: every public method on `ProductCatalog` is called in declaration order, but almost nothing is verified. Code-coverage tools will report high line coverage; in reality, these tests cannot catch regressions.

| Severity | Count |
|----------|-------|
| Critical | 7 |
| High | 1 |
| Medium | 2 |
| Low | 0 |

---

### Critical Findings

#### 1. Coverage-Touching Pattern (systemic — entire class)

The test class methodically calls every public method (`AddProduct`, `GetProduct`, `UpdatePrice`, …, `ImportFromCsv`) with no or trivial assertions. This is the exact pattern you described: 95% coverage, zero verification.

---

#### 2. No Assertions — 5 tests (lines 17–21, 33–36, 39–43, 64–66, 69–74, 85–88)

These tests execute code and return. They **cannot fail** unless an exception is thrown.

| Test method | Line | Problem |
|---|---|---|
| `AddProduct_Works` | 17–21 | Calls `AddProduct`, never checks the product was stored |
| `UpdatePrice_Works` | 33–36 | Calls `UpdatePrice`, never checks the new price |
| `RemoveProduct_Works` | 39–43 | Calls `RemoveProduct`, never checks the product is gone |
| `GetProductCount_Works` | 64–66 | Captures `count` into a local, never asserts its value |
| `ApplyBulkDiscount_Works` | 69–74 | Applies 10% discount to two products, never checks prices changed |
| `ImportFromCsv_Works` | 85–88 | Imports CSV, never checks the resulting product |

**Example fix — `AddProduct_Works`:**

```csharp
// BEFORE (line 17-21)
public void AddProduct_Works()
{
    var product = new Product("SKU-001", "Widget", 9.99m);
    _catalog.AddProduct(product);
}

// AFTER
[TestMethod]
public void AddProduct_ProductCanBeRetrievedBySku()
{
    var product = new Product("SKU-001", "Widget", 9.99m);
    _catalog.AddProduct(product);

    var stored = _catalog.GetProduct("SKU-001");
    Assert.AreEqual("Widget", stored?.Name);
    Assert.AreEqual(9.99m, stored?.Price);
}
```

**Example fix — `ApplyBulkDiscount_Works`:**

```csharp
// BEFORE (line 69-74)
public void ApplyBulkDiscount_Works()
{
    _catalog.AddProduct(new Product("SKU-001", "Widget", 9.99m));
    _catalog.AddProduct(new Product("SKU-002", "Gadget", 19.99m));
    _catalog.ApplyBulkDiscount(0.10m);
}

// AFTER
[TestMethod]
public void ApplyBulkDiscount_ReducesPricesByFraction()
{
