### High Finding

#### 4. No Negative / Edge-Case Tests (entire class)

Every test follows the happy path. The production code has clear edge cases that are untested:

| Scenario | Production behavior | Risk |
|---|---|---|
| `UpdatePrice` for nonexistent SKU | Throws `KeyNotFoundException` (line 14) | Never tested — callers may not handle it |
| `ImportFromCsv` with malformed input | `decimal.Parse` will throw; no validation | Never tested |
| `Search` with empty/null query | Behavior undefined | Never tested |
| `ApplyBulkDiscount` with negative fraction | Would *increase* prices | Never tested |
| `GetProduct` for missing SKU | Returns `null` | Never tested |

**Example fix — add a missing edge-case test:**

```csharp
[TestMethod]
public void UpdatePrice_NonexistentSku_ThrowsKeyNotFoundException()
{
    Assert.ThrowsException<KeyNotFoundException>(
        () => _catalog.UpdatePrice("MISSING", 5.00m));
}
```

